Chairperson of the health portfolio committee, Sibongiseni Dhlomo spoke to #eNCA to discuss this. #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The deployment of Cuban doctors will cost South Africa around R239-million. The specialists (187) have been deployed in various provinces to help fight COVID-19. READ: COVID-19: EC health department refutes scathing report Chairperson of the health portfolio committee, Sibongiseni Dhlomo says the amount is justified. Dhlomo says the main priority is to save lives. "The costs should not be compared to the savings of lives," Dhlomo said. "These are specialists who we don't have in the country, probably they are scarce or in the private sector." South Africa currently has over 50,000 COVID-19 cases with 1,162 deaths. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.